1. The input array `edges` is not null.
2. The length of the input array `edges` is greater than or equal to 2.
3. The length of the input array `edges` is less than or equal to 10^5.
4. Each element in the input array `edges` is an integer.
5. Each element in the input array `edges` is between -1 and n-1, inclusive.
6. The number of nodes in the graph is equal to the length of the input array `edges`.
7. Each node in the graph has at most one outgoing edge.
